[The DRC is challenged by having to combat Ebola and COVID-19 at the same time it must continue to address endemic diseases such as measles, malaria, TB, and malnutrition. This takes resources that the country does not have. It is critical to vaccinate as many children as can be reached to stop the current outbreak of measles. It is one of the most infectious viruses known, with an R0 (reproductive number) of 12-15, significantly higher than SARS-CoV-2, and only vaccination will control its spread.

Also see https://mobile.reuters.com/article/amp/idUSKBN2BP153?__twitter_impression=true. - Mod.LK

